Method Detail

getSchema

public final Schema getSchema()
The Schema of this Expression. Note that this may be null, which indicates that the value is unknown, either because we haven't reached the stage of the compilation where these types are determined, or that the type is actually a native type (and hence, will be dealt with by the OutputLanguage's compiler/interpreter).

getStaticString

public String getStaticString(AlertSink alertSink,
                              String fallback)
Attempts to statically evaluate this Expression as a string. If hasStaticString would return false then an alert will be emitted to the specified AlertSink and the fallback will be returned.

The default implementation of this method generates a StaticAttributeExpectedError and returns the fallback.

hasStaticString

public boolean hasStaticString()
Returns:
true if and only if the Expression can be evaluated statically and it evaluates to a string.

separate

public List<Expression> separate()
Separates a concatenation into a list of its sub-expressions. For non-Concatenations, this just returns a list containing only that expression.
